    {
      "id": 67200,
      "postNumber": 7,
      "createdAt": "2021-10-28T02:22:30.291Z",
      "author": "Flo.DB (Floria de Brosses)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/djbeame\">@djbeame</a> <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/d_h80\">@D_H80</a>, the fact that the majority of emojis can not be added to group/column titles (such as the ones listed in Pedro’s post) is a known issue that our developers are aware of and while we do not have an ETA for the fix just yet, keep an eye out for it in the future! <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/slight_smile.png?v=10\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" /></p>\n<p>Furthermore, while it <em>is</em> currently possible for a select few emojis to be added to (and remain present on) group/column titles, such as <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/no_entry.png?v=10\" title=\":no_entry:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":no_entry:\" /><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/zap.png?v=10\" title=\":zap:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":zap:\" /><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/raised_hand.png?v=10\" title=\":raised_hand:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":raised_hand:\" />, this is not by design.</p>"
    },
